    {
        "content": "<p>The way this is built, it is difficult to get anything else. We basically generate a linker error, so it shows up as a link error.</p>",
        "id": 465620890,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1724817412
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We could change the symbol name to <code>rust_build_error_go_read_docs</code> and then add some docs.</p>",
        "id": 465621021,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1724817449
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My point being, it's hard to know what exactly broke. There has to be some way to go back to the line that generated the issue, otherwise this can be really hard to fix.</p>",
        "id": 466045701,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1724944853
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>IIRC I think GNU LD does tell you the line number?</p>",
